<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,152,323]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,225,251]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Remarks.</emphasis>
Habitus as in 
<figureCitation box="[479,547,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="2.[151,264,2004,2029]" captionTargetBox="[195,1393,747,1968]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[183,1404,733,1976]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Habitus of species of Geodromicus: 1–G. abdominalis (Jilin), 2–G. beibienkoi (Shanxi). Scale bar: 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884791" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884791/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
. Male abdominal tergite VIII as in 
<figureCitation box="[948,1016,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[177,1395,354,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,345,1865]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–7. Male of Geodromicus abdominalis (Jilin): 3–abdominal tergite VIII, 4–abdominal sternite VIII, 5–aedeagus, dorsal view, 6–aedeagus, lateral view, 7–aedeagus, parameral view. Scale bar: 0.2 mm (Figs. 3–4), 0.5 mm (Figs. 5–7)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884793" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884793/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
, and male abdominal sternite VIII as in 
<figureCitation box="[180,248,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[177,1395,354,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,345,1865]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–7. Male of Geodromicus abdominalis (Jilin): 3–abdominal tergite VIII, 4–abdominal sternite VIII, 5–aedeagus, dorsal view, 6–aedeagus, lateral view, 7–aedeagus, parameral view. Scale bar: 0.2 mm (Figs. 3–4), 0.5 mm (Figs. 5–7)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884793" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884793/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
. Aedeagus as in 
<figureCitation box="[434,542,260,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–7" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1890,1915]" captionTargetBox="[177,1395,354,1858]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,345,1865]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–7. Male of Geodromicus abdominalis (Jilin): 3–abdominal tergite VIII, 4–abdominal sternite VIII, 5–aedeagus, dorsal view, 6–aedeagus, lateral view, 7–aedeagus, parameral view. Scale bar: 0.2 mm (Figs. 3–4), 0.5 mm (Figs. 5–7)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884793" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884793/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Figs. 5–7</figureCitation>
. The species is distributed in southern part of Far Eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1191,1266,261,287]" name="Russia" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Russia</collectingCountry>
and Northwest 
<collectingCountry box="[151,222,297,323]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">China</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion box="[233,379,297,323]" country="China" name="Heilongjiang" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Heilongjiang</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[434,482,297,323]" country="China" name="Jilin" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Jilin</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Shavrin, A. V." box="[496,653,297,323]" pageId="3" pageNumber="135" pagination="151 - 190" refId="ref19571" refString="Shavrin, A. V. (2018) The lestevoides species group of the genus Geodromicus Redtenbacher, 1857 (Insecta: Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Omaliinae). Zootaxa, 4378 (2), 151 - 190. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4378.2.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Shavrin 2018</bibRefCitation>
). The distribution of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zerche" authorityYear="2003" box="[888,1060,297,323]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Geodromicus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="135" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abdominalis">
<emphasis box="[888,908,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[922,1060,297,323]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">abdominalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingCountry box="[1096,1163,297,323]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">China</collectingCountry>
is shown in 
<figureCitation box="[1305,1400,297,323]" captionStart="FIGURE 113" captionStartId="34.[151,250,1910,1935]" captionTargetBox="[180,1408,1064,1892]" captionTargetId="figure@34.[180,1408,1064,1892]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURE 113. Distribution of 21 species of Geodromicus in China: 1–G. abdominalis, 2–G. amplissimus, 3–G. aokii, 4–G. beibienkoi, 5–G. chinensis, 6–G. cupreostigma, 7–G. formosanus, 8–G. frigidus, 9–G. hammondi, 10–G. lestevoides, 11–G. magnus sp. n., 12–G. namucuoicus sp. n., 13–G. ohkurai, 14–G. philydroides, 15–G. shii sp. n., 16–G. sibiricus, 17–G. sinuatocollis, 18–G. sinuatus, 19–G. smetanai, 20–G. subquadratus sp. n., 21–G. taiwanensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884852" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884852/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="135">Fig. 113</figureCitation>
